WEBVTT

00:58.120 --> 00:59.560
-Here we go.
-Hello!

00:59.600 --> 01:02.440
Greetings, everybody!
Thank you.

01:02.480 --> 01:04.440
-Thanks very much.
-Hello.

01:05.600 --> 01:07.640
JEREMY: Hello. Hello.

01:07.680 --> 01:09.280
-Hello, everybody.
-Hello.

01:11.160 --> 01:13.680
RICHARD:
Thank you. Thank you.

01:13.720 --> 01:15.480
-JEREMY: Loud!
-That's a big one.

01:15.520 --> 01:17.760
JEREMY: Thank you so much!

01:17.800 --> 01:22.240
Welcome. And in this edition
of the world's most exciting
motoring show...

01:23.720 --> 01:26.040
..a maroon Skoda...

01:26.080 --> 01:29.080
..a silver car
of some sort...

01:29.120 --> 01:32.800
..and an elderly German man
says, "I don't like jumps."

01:32.840 --> 01:34.360
I-I don't like jumps.

01:37.520 --> 01:40.640
-There's a lot.
-It's a good one. Good one.

01:40.680 --> 01:43.640
And there's that
diarrhoea-coloured Audi
as well, isn't there?

01:43.680 --> 01:45.240
Yeah. Yeah, there's that.

01:45.280 --> 01:48.440
-And you kill
a Chinese person.

01:48.480 --> 01:50.840
But we start with
Lamborghini.

01:50.880 --> 01:53.120
They've just launched
a more hard-core,

01:53.160 --> 01:55.720
more exciting version
of the Huracán,

01:55.760 --> 01:58.920
and Richard Hammond
was very keen to try it out.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.400
-I was.
-Yeah, he was.

02:00.440 --> 02:02.680
So we put the air ambulance
on standby...

02:03.840 --> 02:04.960
..and off he went.

02:15.960 --> 02:18.920
RICHARD: Here it is.

02:18.960 --> 02:22.200
It's called
the Huracán Performante.

02:22.240 --> 02:27.560
And whereas the standard
Huracán costs £155,000,

02:27.600 --> 02:32.240
this version comes in
at £208,000.

02:32.280 --> 02:35.680
So what do you get
for the extra £50,000?

02:45.520 --> 02:49.160
Well, to be honest, on paper,
not a lot.

02:49.200 --> 02:51.360
You only get
29 more horsepower,

02:51.400 --> 02:55.160
up from 602 to 631.

02:55.200 --> 02:57.640
And 30 more torques.

02:57.680 --> 02:58.560
Hm.

03:01.600 --> 03:03.160
So, while the original

03:03.200 --> 03:06.320
tops out
at 202 miles an hour,

03:06.360 --> 03:08.880
this can do, erm, the same.

03:11.120 --> 03:12.520
And the 0-60 time

03:12.560 --> 03:16.560
goes down by a whopping
two tenths of a second,

03:16.600 --> 03:20.680
from 3.1 to 2.9.

03:20.720 --> 03:24.160
Now, admittedly,
we are starting
from a very high baseline,

03:24.200 --> 03:28.640
and you have probably
just seen some pictures
of a car going very fast.

03:28.680 --> 03:32.640
But... 55 grand more?

03:32.680 --> 03:34.560
When do you start seeing
something for your money?

03:38.480 --> 03:42.480
Fortunately,
in quite a few places.

03:42.520 --> 03:46.280
For starters,
some proper work has gone
into making the Performante

03:46.320 --> 03:49.760
look more dramatic
than a normal Huracán.

03:49.800 --> 03:53.240
This car has much more of
the get-your-camera-phone-out
appeal

03:53.280 --> 03:55.280
you expect
from a Lamborghini.

03:58.480 --> 04:01.640
I particularly like
the material
this wing's made from.

04:01.680 --> 04:05.000
It's actually
chopped-up carbon fibre
bonded in a resin.

04:05.040 --> 04:07.920
So not only
does it look rather good,
it's also very light.

04:07.960 --> 04:10.400
And because they've
used it all over the place,

04:10.440 --> 04:13.440
they've shaved 40kg off
the weight of the car.

04:13.480 --> 04:16.000
And you would notice that
on a mountain road.

04:18.640 --> 04:22.400
And then we come
to the soundtrack.

04:22.440 --> 04:27.000
Again, if we compare it to
the standard car, the Huracán
makes an OK noise.

04:27.040 --> 04:30.600
But the Performante
comes with a new exhaust,
and that...

04:32.480 --> 04:33.680
Oh-ho!

04:35.320 --> 04:36.480
That is awesome, that is!

04:39.600 --> 04:41.360
Love the sound of a V10.

04:46.160 --> 04:48.480
Like having 10,000 wolves
at your back.

04:56.320 --> 05:01.360
But there's more
to the Performante than
just animalistic howling.

05:01.400 --> 05:06.000
The car is also equipped with
something called Aerodinamica
Lamborghini Attiva,

05:06.040 --> 05:07.720
or ALA for short.

05:07.760 --> 05:11.760
And what it claims to be
is a very clever
aerodynamic system.

05:13.600 --> 05:16.920
Basically, you have moving
flaps in the front spoiler,

05:16.960 --> 05:23.000
and moving air ducts
at the back that control
the airflow to the rear wing.

05:23.040 --> 05:27.160
Now, if you want to go fast
in a straight line, you need
less downforce,

05:27.200 --> 05:31.320
so the ducts open
so they direct more air
under the wing.

05:31.360 --> 05:34.200
Right, so,
fast in a straight line.

05:34.240 --> 05:37.640
That's as good an excuse
for a gratuitous drag race
as we've ever had.

05:39.240 --> 05:42.160
Just a shame there isn't
some local motorist

05:42.200 --> 05:45.840
out for a drive
in a Ferrari 458 Speciale,

05:45.880 --> 05:48.760
or... something...
something that...

05:48.800 --> 05:50.040
Oh, what a stroke of luck!

05:54.960 --> 05:57.040
-Morning.
-Fancy seeing you here.

05:57.080 --> 05:59.320
Yeah. To be honest,
I was just out for a drive

05:59.360 --> 06:01.400
and I stopped to sort of,
you know,

06:01.440 --> 06:03.840
marvel at the mystery
and wonder of God's creation.

06:03.880 --> 06:06.160
Yeah. Well,
I don't know if you're aware,

06:06.200 --> 06:09.840
but you happen to have
pulled up on the start line
of a drag race.

06:09.880 --> 06:11.120
-Yeah.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.320
RICHARD: Seeing as
our cars are so similar,

06:15.360 --> 06:18.920
would you mind
accompanying me to
the other end of this runway

06:18.960 --> 06:21.760
in a drag

06:21.800 --> 06:23.120
-Yeah, all right.
-Excellent.

06:24.280 --> 06:25.640
Good.

06:25.680 --> 06:27.360
It's just worked out
that way today.

06:27.400 --> 06:32.040
That's blind luck that
that man happened to be in...

06:32.080 --> 06:35.360
in... in the logical
competitor for this car.

06:58.880 --> 06:59.960
And we are away!

07:01.120 --> 07:04.080
Avanti!

07:04.120 --> 07:08.560
That aero now doing
its business to make this
thing as fast as possible...

07:08.600 --> 07:10.160
in a straight line.

07:10.200 --> 07:11.240
And, dear God!

07:16.880 --> 07:19.080
-Ha!
-Oh, no!

07:19.120 --> 07:24.560
I beat the local man
in his 458 Speciale,
by some considerable margin.

07:28.080 --> 07:31.760
But the Lambo's clever aero
system is equally impressive

07:31.800 --> 07:35.760
when you get
to the end of a straight
and arrive at a corner.

07:41.240 --> 07:43.240
Oh!

07:43.280 --> 07:46.000
As I go into a corner,
I need more downforce
to give me more grip.

07:52.440 --> 07:55.760
So the flaps and ducts are
adjusting to do just that.

08:00.920 --> 08:03.160
It's pressing down,
it's giving it grip.

08:04.640 --> 08:07.520
More than that, it can
operate individual sides

08:07.560 --> 08:12.480
so it can work individual
wheels mid-corner
to dial up the grip.

08:14.160 --> 08:16.440
That's clever.
Very, very clever.

08:20.440 --> 08:25.000
And let me give you some hard
evidence of just how clever.

08:25.040 --> 08:29.360
The Porsche 918, my favourite
out-of-this-world hypercar,

08:29.400 --> 08:33.200
went round the Nurburgring in
six minutes and 57 seconds.

08:33.240 --> 08:35.840
This thing,
five seconds quicker.

08:43.040 --> 08:48.960
As a driving machine,
the Performante
is one hell of an experience.

08:49.000 --> 08:52.200
But there's
even more to it than that.

08:52.240 --> 08:55.360
What Lamborghini
have done with this
is hit a real sweet spot.

08:55.400 --> 08:57.800
It can corner like a race car

08:57.840 --> 09:00.640
and shatter trees
with its engine noise,

09:00.680 --> 09:04.160
but it hasn't been turned
into some hard-core
track-day abomination.

09:04.200 --> 09:07.040
I've got air-con and Apple
connecty stuff in here.

09:07.080 --> 09:10.880
In the comfort sense,
it's very much like driving
a standard Huracán.

09:13.160 --> 09:17.920
And that last point is why
this car is so special.

09:17.960 --> 09:22.840
A lifetime ago, on a car show
in a galaxy far, far away,

09:22.880 --> 09:27.880
I reviewed the original
Huracán and was left
feeling a bit sad

09:27.920 --> 09:31.760
because it lacked that drama,
that thrill-delivery system

09:31.800 --> 09:34.560
that a Lamborghini
should have and be.

09:36.520 --> 09:39.680
Well, finally it's here.
The whole package
is complete.

09:39.720 --> 09:43.280
This is what the Huracán
should have been
from the start.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.040
It's brilliant.

10:03.040 --> 10:05.040
RICHARD: That was
a really... amazing thing.

10:05.080 --> 10:08.880
I don't see how Ferrari
always lose a race...

10:08.920 --> 10:12.200
when it's some punter's
car, and when they provide
the car, they win.

10:12.240 --> 10:13.440
RICHARD: Amazing, isn't it?

10:13.480 --> 10:15.280
I actually, erm...

10:15.320 --> 10:17.400
I drove a Performante
the other day,

10:17.440 --> 10:19.640
and I pulled out
to overtake a Peugeot,

10:19.680 --> 10:22.640
put my foot down,
and the noise was so enormous

10:22.680 --> 10:26.520
I genuinely believed the
engine had actually exploded.

10:26.560 --> 10:28.720
-I've never heard
a sound like it.

10:28.760 --> 10:30.400
It is pretty loud.

10:30.440 --> 10:32.120
But it's not pretty loud,
it's incredibly loud.

10:32.160 --> 10:35.520
It can't possibly pass any,
you know, regulations.

10:35.560 --> 10:38.200
-It doesn't need to be,
it's Italian.
-It is Italian, that's true.

10:38.240 --> 10:40.080
It's also...
It's also fantastic.

10:40.120 --> 10:43.000
I think I'm right in...
No, I know I'm right
in saying

10:43.040 --> 10:45.960
it's currently my favourite
supercar of the moment.

10:46.000 --> 10:47.200
Oh, it's definitely mine.
Supercar.

10:47.240 --> 10:48.920
Absolutely adorable,
it really is.

10:48.960 --> 10:53.560
Anyway, we must now find
how fast it goes round
the Eboladrome.

10:55.240 --> 10:56.520
-Come on, let's have it!

10:57.840 --> 10:59.480
JEREMY: And she's off!

10:59.520 --> 11:02.240
A searing start,
and a ferocious howl

11:02.280 --> 11:06.120
as the Huracán powers
onto the Isn't Straight.

11:06.160 --> 11:10.160
Grabbing at the gears to keep
that amazing V10 on song.

11:10.200 --> 11:13.120
And carrying some serious
speed through there.

11:13.160 --> 11:17.400
No let-up as she drives down
towards Your Name Here.

11:19.120 --> 11:21.280
Despite being
the hard-core model,

11:21.320 --> 11:24.760
the Performante
is still four-wheel-drive
like the standard Huracán.

11:24.800 --> 11:29.080
And that clearly translates
into serious mechanical grip.

11:29.120 --> 11:35.080
Now, unleashing all
631 horsepower for the blast
back down the Isn't.

11:35.120 --> 11:39.920
You really can't beat
a normally-aspirated engine
for sheer visceral wailing.

11:39.960 --> 11:41.960
It's superb.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.080
Old Lady's House.

11:44.120 --> 11:47.800
Grip, and that
active aero trickery
staving off understeer.

11:47.840 --> 11:50.960
On the bumpy run down
to Substation.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
Is it going to be OK
through there?

11:53.040 --> 11:57.360
Yep, absolutely
no problem working
the carbon-ceramic brakes.

11:57.400 --> 11:59.760
Flies round Field of Sheep
and across the line!

12:01.560 --> 12:03.920
-That looked good.
That looked fast.
-It looks quick.

12:03.960 --> 12:05.800
-Yeah, that's it.

12:07.520 --> 12:09.680
-That was properly...
darting.
-It looked it.

12:09.720 --> 12:11.240
Anyway,

12:11.280 --> 12:13.280
we must now find out

12:13.320 --> 12:15.200
how far up the board

12:15.240 --> 12:16.680
the Huracán goes.

12:16.720 --> 12:19.600
RICHARD: Oh, hello.
Oh, hang on. Oh-ho!

12:19.640 --> 12:22.520
-JEREMY: Bloody hell.

12:22.560 --> 12:27.440
One sixteen-eight - that's
the fastest road-legal car
we've ever had round there.

12:27.480 --> 12:29.920
-It's not road-legal.
-It's Italian.

12:29.960 --> 12:32.200
-Same thing.
-Everything in Italian's
road-legal.

12:32.240 --> 12:36.560
Anyway, it is now time
for us to plant
some daffodils of opinion

12:36.600 --> 12:41.320
on the roundabout of chat
at the end of
Conversation Street.

12:48.200 --> 12:49.160
Sorry.

12:50.760 --> 12:53.560
-So sorry.

12:53.600 --> 12:56.080
That's the best thing
that's going to come
out of your mouth

12:56.120 --> 12:57.440
for the next seven minutes.

12:58.680 --> 13:00.040
Ouch!

13:00.080 --> 13:03.520
So erm, conversation,
sticking with supercars.

13:03.560 --> 13:07.440
Many new ones
have arrived recently,
and we have one here.

13:07.480 --> 13:10.360
If you have a look,
that is the Devel Sixteen.

13:10.400 --> 13:14.600
Now, that's a 12.3-litre
V16 quad-turbo engine.

13:14.640 --> 13:17.080
It's two Chevy engines
glued together.

13:17.120 --> 13:22.560
And it has a top speed,
according to the makers,
of 320 miles an hour.

13:22.600 --> 13:24.040
Really?

13:24.080 --> 13:25.600
-Three hundred and--
-That's what they say.

13:25.640 --> 13:26.840
You can test that one,
Hammond.

13:28.800 --> 13:31.200
-That's what they say.

13:31.240 --> 13:33.160
Anyway, if you don't fancy
the Devel Sixteen,

13:33.200 --> 13:37.800
you could try the
Ikeya Formula IF-02RDS,

13:37.840 --> 13:41.200
the Apollo Intensa Emozione,

13:41.240 --> 13:44.160
the er, Dallara Stradale,

13:44.200 --> 13:46.920
the er, Aspark Owl.

13:46.960 --> 13:48.880
What Owl?

13:48.920 --> 13:51.800
-The Aspark Owl, yes.
-You can't call a car an Owl.

13:51.840 --> 13:54.480
-JAMES: The Vencer Sarthe,

13:54.520 --> 13:56.640
the Arrinera Hussarya,

13:56.680 --> 13:59.600
the Mazzanti
Evantra Millecavalli,

13:59.640 --> 14:02.040
and the Hennessey Venom.

14:02.080 --> 14:04.520
No, I'm sorry, this is just
ridiculous. Seriously,
they're all new supercars?

14:04.560 --> 14:06.680
-They're all new supercars.
-That's absurd!

14:06.720 --> 14:08.720
-And then, from America...
-Oh, God!

14:08.760 --> 14:13.520
..there's the Glickenhaus
SCG 004S.

14:13.560 --> 14:17.080
And from Denmark,
the Zenvo TS1 GT.

14:17.120 --> 14:20.400
Right, we've got the idea.
Every single person in the
world has suddenly decided,

14:20.440 --> 14:22.400
"You know, I can make
a supercar myself."

14:22.440 --> 14:23.840
Yeah, it looks that way.
Yeah.

14:23.880 --> 14:25.800
The problem I've got
with all of this is

14:25.840 --> 14:27.720
it's not like we're
spoiled for choice already.

14:27.760 --> 14:29.680
I mean, you've got Ferrari,
Lamborghini,

14:29.720 --> 14:33.600
you've got Bugatti,
McLaren, Ford, even Audi.

14:33.640 --> 14:36.680
Yeah, but what if you want
a supercar with no heritage

14:36.720 --> 14:38.120
that's built
in someone's shed?

14:38.160 --> 14:40.120
If that's
what you really want.

14:40.160 --> 14:42.480
-And that you can't
get serviced anywhere.
-RICHARD: Exactly.

14:42.520 --> 14:45.400
Did any car there
appeal to anyone here?

14:47.600 --> 14:50.160
You'd all rather have
a Lamborghini Performante
than anything there?

14:50.200 --> 14:52.440
So that's total failure
for all those people.

14:52.480 --> 14:55.600
What you've just
looked at there
is 27 future bankruptcies.

14:57.480 --> 15:01.640
Now, we have always
argued that women,
whatever they say,

15:01.680 --> 15:06.440
are impressed when a man
performs a perfectly executed
handbrake turn.

15:06.480 --> 15:08.960
Oh, it's absolutely true.

15:09.000 --> 15:11.120
We've all been watching
Sir Attenborough's fish
programme, haven't we, yeah?

15:11.160 --> 15:13.200
Yeah, Blue Planet .
Unbelievable, OK?

15:13.240 --> 15:15.680
Now, the thing is, every
single week you see, OK,

15:15.720 --> 15:17.880
man fish comes along
with his lady fish there.

15:17.920 --> 15:22.040
Man fish can make his face
swell up - it's huge -
like a satellite dish.

15:22.080 --> 15:24.200
Lady fish: "I'm not bothered.
I'm not bothered."

15:24.240 --> 15:26.440
-But she is. She is.
-RICHARD: Yeah.

15:26.480 --> 15:28.840
And then she's going,
"I like his huge face,"

15:28.880 --> 15:32.480
and then they do sex,
or whatever it is fish do,
and then they have babies.

15:32.520 --> 15:34.920
Now, that massive face
that a fish can do,

15:34.960 --> 15:37.200
that's basically the same
as the handbrake turn.

15:37.240 --> 15:39.440
-All those birds
that dance about.

15:39.480 --> 15:41.720
We've got the handbrake,
birds can dance about.

15:41.760 --> 15:45.080
-It's all part of nature's
dance of love.
-Exactly.

15:45.120 --> 15:49.040
But the problem has been, of
course, most modern cars now
have electronic handbrakes.

15:49.080 --> 15:51.280
You can't do a handbrake turn
with one of those.

15:51.320 --> 15:53.000
That's why Tinder's
become so big.

15:53.040 --> 15:55.000
-Yeah, you have to...

15:55.040 --> 15:57.680
You have to swipe right
because you can't
slide left any more.

15:57.720 --> 16:00.240
-That's what's going on.
-Well, so that's been
the problem.

16:00.280 --> 16:03.080
With electronic handbrakes
we can't conduct
this mating ritual.

16:03.120 --> 16:06.920
Ford have noticed this,
given it some thought, and
they've come up with this.

16:06.960 --> 16:09.600
It's an after-market part
that you fit to your car.

16:09.640 --> 16:11.880
They call it the drift stick.

16:11.920 --> 16:14.400
-Oh, they ought to call it
the love handle.
-Yeah.

16:16.080 --> 16:18.040
But the point is, what it
does, it overrides the ABS,

16:18.080 --> 16:20.880
and you can actually
perform proper
handbrake turns in that.

16:20.920 --> 16:22.560
Girls are going to say,
if you pull that,

16:22.600 --> 16:24.280
"That was ridiculous
and you frightened me."

16:24.320 --> 16:26.360
-What they actually
mean is, "I'm hot."
-Yeah.

16:26.400 --> 16:28.760
-Come on. Yeah, admit it.

16:28.800 --> 16:31.280
-You're impressed by
a handbrake turn, aren't you?
-Just the thought of it.

16:31.320 --> 16:33.320
If you say no,
that's just part of it.

16:33.360 --> 16:35.560
I've never been
in a car with...

16:35.600 --> 16:37.880
You've never been in a car
with someone who's done
a handbrake turn?

16:37.920 --> 16:39.760
-Oh, hello!

16:39.800 --> 16:40.960
JEREMY: Ooh!

16:42.240 --> 16:44.080
Are you together?

16:44.120 --> 16:48.000
RICHARD: What are you doing,
man

16:48.040 --> 16:50.720
What is wrong with you?
How do you...?

16:54.720 --> 16:57.280
You drove here today,
huge fields everywhere.

16:57.320 --> 16:59.240
You didn't think,
"I'll give it some of that"?

16:59.280 --> 17:01.000
RICHARD: Get out there
and impress her.

17:01.040 --> 17:02.720
On the way out...
Just mind the sheep.

17:04.200 --> 17:06.880
Right, listen.
Bentley has announced

17:06.920 --> 17:09.640
a new version
of their big four-by-four,
the Bentayga, OK?

17:09.680 --> 17:11.960
Er... Which they say
is for shooting enthusiasts.

17:12.000 --> 17:15.000
We've got a picture here,
look. It's got this
kind of chest in the back

17:15.040 --> 17:18.240
which has, you know,
space for your guns
and refreshments, and so on.

17:18.280 --> 17:24.080
However, I know that whoever
designed that has never been
shooting in their lives.

17:24.120 --> 17:26.360
How do you know?

17:26.400 --> 17:28.880
Well, because if we examine
the refreshments that have
been photographed here,

17:28.920 --> 17:31.720
you will find that they
have fitted it with...

17:31.760 --> 17:34.840
rose lemonade
and elderflower juice.

17:34.880 --> 17:37.120
-Now, I'm sorry to say...

17:37.160 --> 17:40.520
No, I'm sorry to have to say
this, but has anyone here
been shooting ever?

17:42.280 --> 17:45.760
As you will know, a shooting
day is an armed drinks party.

